pair.value: Create a new purchase order for a customer

acp.name: Subject
acp.a:expr: ="Thank you for your order / Order # " & pv!Order.OrderNum

message-trigger.name: ReceiveAutoGenerateMsg
message-trigger.desc: This message event is used by the Data Generator to auto generate Orders

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr: =" has created a new order for " & pv!Order.Customer.Name & " / Order # " & pv!Order.OrderNum & " / Order Total: " & dollar(pv!Order.Total, 2, 0)

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr: =" has updated order for " & pv!Order.Customer.Name & " / Order # " & pv!Order.OrderNum & " / Order Total: " & dollar(pv!Order.Total, 2, 0) & " / New Status: " & pv!Order.Status

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr: =" has updated order for " & pv!Order.Customer.Name & " / Order # " & pv!Order.OrderNum & " / Order Total: " & dollar(pv!Order.Total, 2, 0) & " / New Status: " & pv!Order.Status

acp.name: Message
acp.a:expr: ="Order " & pv!Order.OrderNum & " is complete and has been received by " & pv!Order.Customer.Name

annotation.text: This Timer event would be replaced with your integration to your shipment provider. Track the shipment and then trigger the event to complete the order
